data.title: Schwartzkopffstrasse, Kreisfreie Stadt Berlin Podcast
data.meta_description: Schwartzkopffstrasse is a residential street in the Oranienburger suburb in the Mitte district of Berlin. The street was named in 1889 after the entrepreneur Louis Schwartzkopff, who ran Berliner Maschinenbau AG in the neighboring Chausseestrasse from 1851 to 1867. Unlike the namesake of the neig...
